<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4223] Support the ability to return a set of rows using Coprocessors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4223</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently HBase supports returning the results of aggregation operations using coprocessors with the AggregationClient. It would be useful to include a client and implementation which would return a set of rows which match a certain criteria using coprocessors as well. We have a use case in our business process for this. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have an initial implementation of this, which I&apos;ve attached. The only limitation that we&apos;ve found is that it cannot be used to return very large sets of rows. If the result set is very large, it would probably require some sort of pagination.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
